### Detailed answer

I have discovered a method which I was not aware of: [DatabaseConnection.inConnection()][1]. The `DatabaseConnection` interface inherits it from `ConnectionAccessor`:

&gt; Execute a callback Function within a Connection scope. The function is responsible for creating a Mono. The connection is released after the Mono terminates (or the subscription is cancelled). Connection resources must not be passed outside of the Function closure, otherwise resources may get defunct.

